### 1. Choose the Right Algorithm
- **For General Use**: `Arrays.sort()` or `Collections.sort()`. These methods use a tuned version of the TimSort algorithm (a hybrid sorting algorithm derived from merge sort and insertion sort) which is efficient for most data types.
